## CDN / Edge Cache

### What to Cache at the Edge

```
CACHE (static, same for everyone):
  - CSS, JS bundles (with content hash)
  - Images, fonts, icons
  - Public pages (static pages, infrequently changing content)
  - API responses for public data (with short TTL)

DON'T CACHE (dynamic, user-specific):
  - API responses with user data
  - Auth endpoints
  - Pages behind login (unless using edge auth)
  - Real-time data (WebSocket, SSE)
```

### Rules

- **Purge on deploy** - clear CDN cache when deploying new static assets
- **Use cache tags** - tag cached items by type so you can selectively purge ("purge all uploaded images")
- **Regional caching** - CDN serves from nearest edge location (no config needed, built-in)
- **HTTPS only** at the edge - never cache over plain HTTP
- **Custom cache keys** - include relevant query params, exclude tracking params

---

## Application Cache (Redis / In-Memory)

This layer is the per-user-aware server cache (Redis or in-process), keyed explicitly per user where needed. It is NOT the framework Tier 2 data cache (see Framework Data Cache below), which is shared across requests and must never hold user-scoped data.

### What to Cache

```
CACHE (expensive to compute, changes infrequently):
  - User session data (permissions, basic display fields) - keyed per user (e.g. users:permissions:user-123), never in a shared/global key
  - Configuration / feature flags
  - Aggregated data (summary stats, report data)
  - Frequently accessed records (hot data, popular items)
  - External API responses (geocoding, exchange rates)
  - Computed results (expensive calculations, report data)

DON'T CACHE (changes frequently or is critical to be real-time):
  - Real-time presence / online status
  - Counters that must be real-time accurate
  - Frequently changing counters (if accuracy is critical)
  - Critical real-time values (if accuracy is critical)
```

### Cache Key Naming

```
Format: {service}:{entity}:{identifier}:{variant}

Examples:
  actors:metadata:user-123
  users:permissions:user-123
  resources:list:group-456:page-1
  stats:summary:scope-789:daily
  config:feature-flags:global
  external:exchange-rates:USD
```

**Rules:**
- Descriptive, hierarchical keys (easy to debug and selectively flush)
- Include all parameters that affect the cached value
- Consistent prefix per service (users:*, resources:*, stats:*)

### TTL (Time-To-Live) Guidelines

**Principle:** Set cache TTLs based on how frequently the underlying data changes and how stale the consumer can tolerate.

[REFERENCE] Typical TTL values by data type:

```
Data Type                          TTL
────────────────────────────────────────────────
Feature flags / config             5 minutes
User permissions                   5-15 minutes
Summary/aggregate data              1-5 minutes
Basic display fields for actors     15-30 minutes
External API responses             1-60 minutes (depends on source)
Static reference data              1-24 hours
Search autocomplete suggestions    1 hour
```

**Rule**: Pick the shortest TTL you can tolerate. When in doubt, shorter is safer.

